==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Covin
<hw>Cov"in</hw> <pr>(k?v"?n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OF.
<ets>covine</ets>, <ets>covaine</ets>, fr. <ets>covenir</ets> to agree.
See <er>Covenant</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>A
collusive agreement between two or more persons to prejudice a
third.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Deceit; fraud; artifice.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Coving</ent>⟦br⟧
